<section class="aerys-agitation" id="agitation" aria-labelledby="agitation-title">
  <div class="container">

    <span class="sec-label sec-label--dark">Why Nothing Has Worked</span>
    <h2 id="agitation-title" class="aerys-agitation__headline">
      You&rsquo;ve tried to fix this.<br>Here&rsquo;s exactly <span class="hi">why it failed.</span>
    </h2>
    <p class="aerys-agitation__sub">If you&rsquo;ve been exhausted long enough, you&rsquo;ve already tried something. Most people have. And most people have quietly given up &mdash; not because sleep can&rsquo;t be fixed, but because the solutions they tried were built on the wrong premise.</p>

    <div class="aerys-agitation__fails">

      <div class="aerys-fail-card">
        <div class="aerys-fail-card__label">
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg>
          Failed Solution
        </div>
        <h3 class="aerys-fail-card__title">The CPAP Machine</h3>
        <p class="aerys-fail-card__body">Addresses airflow after the airway collapses. Does not address the open mouth that caused the collapse. Loud, invasive, and requires a mask strapped to your face. Fifty percent of patients abandon it within 90 days. The ones who keep it report sleeping &ldquo;fine&rdquo; the way you sleep fine in a hospital &mdash; technically unconscious, not actually rested.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="aerys-fail-card">
        <div class="aerys-fail-card__label">
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg>
          Failed Solution
        </div>
        <h3 class="aerys-fail-card__title">Standard Mouth Tape</h3>
        <p class="aerys-fail-card__body">The right idea. A catastrophically wrong material. The adhesive in most sleep strips is the same class of industrial acrylic used in packaging tape. It leaves black residue. It causes contact dermatitis. It pulls skin and facial hair on removal. People quit after three nights and decide mouth taping &ldquo;doesn&rsquo;t work.&rdquo; Mouth taping works. The tape just doesn&rsquo;t.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="aerys-fail-card">
        <div class="aerys-fail-card__label">
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg>
          Failed Solution
        </div>
        <h3 class="aerys-fail-card__title">Mouthguards &amp; Oral Devices</h3>
        <p class="aerys-fail-card__body">Address teeth grinding and forward jaw positioning. They do not create a lip seal. They do not restore nasal breathing. They solve a different problem at significant cost and significant discomfort &mdash; and leave the root cause completely untouched.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="aerys-agitation__twist">
      <p class="aerys-agitation__twist-text">The delivery mechanism was broken. Not your sleep.</p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="aerys-agitation__cost-title">But there is a longer cost to not fixing this.</h3>

    <div class="aerys-agitation__cost-items">

      <div class="aerys-agitation__cost-item">
        <div class="aerys-agitation__cost-dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <p class="aerys-agitation__cost-text"><strong style="color:rgba(255,255,255,.85)">Chronically elevated cortisol</strong> &mdash; caused nightly by the physiological stress of oxygen-reduced sleep &mdash; breaks down muscle tissue, promotes fat retention, accelerates cognitive aging, and suppresses immune function. This is not a minor inconvenience. This is your body aging faster than it should, night after night, while you lie completely still.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="aerys-agitation__cost-item">
        <div class="aerys-agitation__cost-dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <p class="aerys-agitation__cost-text"><strong style="color:rgba(255,255,255,.85)">Snoring is not just noise.</strong> Each vibration is your airway collapsing and recovering. Each collapse is a micro-arousal. Across a seven-hour night, these add up to dozens of partial awakenings your brain logs as threats. You may not remember waking. Your biology does.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="aerys-agitation__cost-item">
        <div class="aerys-agitation__cost-dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <p class="aerys-agitation__cost-text"><strong style="color:rgba(255,255,255,.85)">The jaw and facial structural changes</strong> from years of open-mouth sleep take years to address &mdash; not weeks. Every night you don&rsquo;t fix this, the baseline gets harder to recover from.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

